manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: 20W USB-C Fast Charging Connect your iPhone 13 to the USB-C port to charge up to 53% in 30 minutes. Easy Wall Mounting Equipped with 2 keyhole mounting slots on the back, so you can easily mount the power strip to your wall. Space for Larger Plugs The outlets on the outer edges of the power strip are 1.5 in apart so you can plug in larger adapters with ease.

Model Number: A9192 Anker 351 Power Strip Power All Your Essentials Huge Expansion Turn a single outlet into 12 AC outlets, 1 USB-C port, and 2 USB-A ports to power up a wide range of appliances and mobile devices. Power Your Mobile Devices: Use the 20W USB-C port to charge up your iPhone at high-speed, or use the 2 USB-A ports to power up your earbuds and other accessories. Superior Safety Our 8-Point Safety System safeguards your connected devices with a range of safety features including surge protection, grounded protection, fire resistance, and more. For Large and Small Plugs Some power bricks are so big that they can block other outlets, but not with Anker 351 Power Strip. We've added extra space between outlets to make room for all your plugs, both large and small. Specs USB-C and USB-A Output: USB-C: 5V 3A/9V 2.22A/12V 1.67A (20W max) USB-A: 5V 3A (2.4A max per port) 2 USB-A ports and 1 USB-C port share 5V 3A Dimensions: 24.5 × 10.6 × 2.6 cm Weight: 650.8 g Note: 1. 20W USB-C charging is only available when the 2 USB-A ports are not in use. 2. If you have a USB-A to Lightning or USB-A to MagSafe cable connected to the USB-A port, please disconnect and then reconnect the cable before charging. 3. The USB-A port does not support Quick Charge 3.0. Devices equipped with Quick Charge, such as the Galaxy series, will charge at regular speed. 4. Quick Charge and Power Delivery technologies are not supported on the USB-C port when using both ports simultaneously. 5. The USB ports of this product are not compatible with laptops.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent power strip!
reviews.reviewText: Like most people, I’ve had power strips my whole life, but I have to tell you this is one of the best I have ever used. I got the white one and it blends in perfectly and there are so many outlets to use and spaced so far apart I got all of my computer and accessories and other appliances in my office plugged into this one outlet very easily with plenty of room and plenty of extra outlets to use in the future. . I love the 2100J surge protection that I get with this power strip, and I like the way it plugs into the wall flat.. it seems silly to get excited about a power strip, but I am it looks so nice and works so well if I could give it six stars I would!! And Anker is good stuff! I’m very happy with this product!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Power Up Your Devices with Confidence
reviews.reviewText: In a world where our reliance on technology grows day by day, finding the right surge protector is more critical than ever. Anker, a name synonymous with reliability and innovation, has delivered a game-changing solution with their Surge Protector Power Strip. Boasting 12 outlets, 1 USB-C, and 2 USB ports, along with a slew of user-friendly features, this power strip ensures your devices stay safe, powered, and ready to go. With its flat plug, 5-foot extension cord, and 20W USB-C charging capability, it's a powerhouse deserving of its five-star rating.**Protection and Peace of Mind (5/5):**First and foremost, the Anker Surge Protector Power Strip is designed to safeguard your valuable devices. With a robust 2100J surge protection rating, it shields against power spikes and surges, offering peace of mind that your electronics remain safe from unexpected electrical fluctuations. TUV certification further underscores its commitment to quality and safety, assuring users that this power strip meets stringent international standards.**Ample Outlets and USB Ports (5/5):**Never worry about running out of outlets again. This power strip boasts 12 AC outlets, allowing you to plug in all your gadgets, chargers, and appliances simultaneously. Additionally, the inclusion of 1 USB-C port and 2 USB ports eliminates the need for bulky adapters, making it a one-stop solution for all your charging needs. Whether you're charging your iPhone 15/15 Plus/15 Pro/15 Pro Max or any other USB-powered device, this power strip has you covered.**USB-C Charging Powerhouse (5/5):**The 20W USB-C port is a standout feature, providing fast and efficient charging for your devices. With the rapid evolution of USB-C technology, this power strip future-proofs your charging setup. Whether you're charging your smartphone, tablet, or laptop, the USB-C port ensures that your devices get the power they need quickly and safely.**Smart and Convenient Design (5/5):**Anker has paid attention to detail in the design of this power strip. The flat plug is a space-saving feature, allowing you to position your furniture and appliances closer to the wall. The 5-foot extension cord offers flexibility in placing the power strip where it's needed most, reducing clutter and enhancing convenience. The on/off switch provides an easy way to conserve energy when your devices aren't in use.**Versatile for Home and Office (5/5):**Whether you're using it at home or in the office, this power strip excels. Its sleek and modern design seamlessly blends into any environment. With its ability to accommodate a multitude of devices, it's the perfect companion for your workstation, entertainment center, or home office setup.**Final Thoughts (5/5):**In conclusion, the Anker Surge Protector Power Strip is a testament to Anker's commitment to quality, safety, and innovation. With its robust surge protection, ample outlets and USB ports, USB-C charging capability, and thoughtful design features, it is a versatile powerhouse that will enhance your daily life.No matter if you're safeguarding your valuable electronics, charging your devices efficiently, or simply decluttering your living space, this power strip is the solution you've been looking for. It's not just a power strip; it's a safeguard for your devices and a boost to your productivity. The Anker Surge Protector Power Strip is unquestionably deserving of its five-star rating—it's time to power up with confidence.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great power strip
reviews.reviewText: This thing is awesome. It has plenty of ports spaced very well. I can fit numerous power bricks with little problem, and the built in USB ports are fast charging and really solid. I also like that it has padded rubber feet and a high quality finish. It's my primary power strip for my electronics lab bench and it does it's job perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars USB ports failed after 1 month, but excellent customer support (updated)
reviews.reviewText: Update: I originally gave this a 1-star after my surge protector's USB ports failed. However, customer service was kind enough to assist me with this and provided me with a new one. So far, I have used the new one for about 2 weeks, which has worked fine so far, so I updated it to 4 stars. If it fails sooner than expected, I will update again accordingly.This surge protector has a very nice compact form factor, including the presence of USB-C and two USB-A ports, which are the reasons I bought it to replace one which had served me well for nearly 20 years.Unfortunately, they have become unreliable after a month, literally a day after my return window expired. While the manufacturer does state that there is insufficient power to use USB-C with the USB-A ports simultaneously, this no longer has the juice to even power USB-A by itself. I expected much better from Anker.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A lot of outlets but usb is limited
reviews.reviewText: Like most Anker products this feels well made and does what it is supposed to do. Only gripe is that plugging two devices into USB ports doesn't work (iPad mini and iPhone 14) as there isn't enough available power to meet minimum amps for both at the same time. Not a big deal for me but a bit disappointing.
